WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.800
If I'm Jason Tatum, I'm looking at ways to improve my game.

00:00:03.800 --> 00:00:05.320
I'm really good at posting up.

00:00:05.320 --> 00:00:06.640
I'm really good in isolation.

00:00:06.640 --> 00:00:08.359
I'm really good at creating opportunities.

00:00:08.359 --> 00:00:10.120
But where I could get better is the opportunities

00:00:10.120 --> 00:00:11.080
to catch and shoot.

00:00:12.720 --> 00:00:15.280
I'm popping out to catch, right?

00:00:15.280 --> 00:00:17.519
I'm catching, I'm looking to attack off the catch.

00:00:17.519 --> 00:00:21.679
I think I can do a better job of sliding away quicker

00:00:21.679 --> 00:00:23.719
and right into a shot.

00:00:23.719 --> 00:00:25.000
All right, so if I'm moving faster here,

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:27.160
I slide into this little pocket area.

00:00:27.160 --> 00:00:29.120
Move, don't let the catch the ball here.

00:00:29.120 --> 00:00:31.679
Curl off, slide right into this pocket area,

00:00:31.679 --> 00:00:33.480
just underneath Banes.

00:00:33.480 --> 00:00:35.960
That should be a good catch and shoot opportunity, right?

00:00:35.960 --> 00:00:38.120
Because if you see Nance is playing off, right?

00:00:38.120 --> 00:00:40.280
He's protecting against penetration.

00:00:40.280 --> 00:00:43.000
So if I'm able to slide off of this

00:00:43.960 --> 00:00:45.519
and come down into this pocket here,

00:00:45.519 --> 00:00:47.159
so you can't throw that pass right now

00:00:47.159 --> 00:00:48.120
because I don't want to catch it there.

00:00:48.120 --> 00:00:51.040
I want to catch it right here in this pocket here, right?

00:00:51.040 --> 00:00:53.960
So I'm hiding behind Banes so my man can't get to me.

00:00:53.960 --> 00:00:55.680
He's got a bad angle to get to me, right?

00:00:55.680 --> 00:00:57.079
So that frees me up for a second

00:00:57.079 --> 00:00:58.840
to be able to shoot that jump shot.

00:00:58.840 --> 00:01:01.800
So I curl around that, slide into this pocket,

00:01:01.800 --> 00:01:02.920
and that should be a jump shot

00:01:02.920 --> 00:01:04.760
because Nance is not playing me to catch and shoot.

00:01:04.760 --> 00:01:06.920
He's playing me to drive, right?

00:01:06.920 --> 00:01:08.120
He's cushioning.

00:01:08.120 --> 00:01:09.400
So I got to get into that pocket

00:01:09.400 --> 00:01:10.800
and look for that jump shot.

00:01:15.800 --> 00:01:17.480
No, this would be a bucket.

00:01:17.480 --> 00:01:20.600
I'm coming out too wide here.

00:01:23.920 --> 00:01:25.719
That's a jump shot right there.

00:01:25.719 --> 00:01:26.960
Hide behind that screen.

00:01:27.960 --> 00:01:30.000
If I come up too high here,

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:33.680
I give my man a right angle to get to me, right?

00:01:33.680 --> 00:01:35.920
Coming up here, that's the right, he can close out to me.

00:01:35.920 --> 00:01:38.200
Instead of being here, if I move back just a little bit,

00:01:38.200 --> 00:01:40.920
just behind the screen, he can't get to me.

00:01:40.920 --> 00:01:42.200
I know he's cheating it, right?

00:01:42.200 --> 00:01:44.240
So he's trying to shortcut it.

00:01:44.240 --> 00:01:45.360
So when he tries to shortcut it,

00:01:45.360 --> 00:01:48.160
it's important that I hide right behind that screen there.

00:01:48.160 --> 00:01:50.880
You simplify the game, simplify the game, catch and shoot.

00:01:50.880 --> 00:01:53.040
But coming all the way out here at this angle

00:01:53.040 --> 00:01:56.320
makes it very easy for the defense to close out to me.

00:01:56.320 --> 00:01:59.640
But if I can drop my catch down

00:01:59.640 --> 00:02:01.760
and catch it just behind the screen,

00:02:03.320 --> 00:02:05.400
instead of catching it out here,

00:02:05.400 --> 00:02:07.680
now that should be an open opportunity.

00:02:07.680 --> 00:02:10.080
Should be an easy catch and shoot right there.

00:02:11.760 --> 00:02:13.520
So to learn from some of the players

00:02:13.520 --> 00:02:14.480
that came before me,

00:02:14.480 --> 00:02:16.120
I'd probably look at Richard Hamilton

00:02:16.120 --> 00:02:17.520
when he was with the Detroit Pistons

00:02:17.520 --> 00:02:19.400
and how he used these screens a lot,

00:02:19.400 --> 00:02:20.800
and how he moved without the ball

00:02:20.800 --> 00:02:24.719
and how he got himself into these little pocket areas

00:02:24.719 --> 00:02:26.840
off the screen to be able to catch and shoot.

00:02:26.840 --> 00:02:29.039
Understanding how his defender's playing him,

00:02:29.039 --> 00:02:30.680
to be able to curl off of an action

00:02:30.680 --> 00:02:32.199
and get back door layups.

00:02:32.199 --> 00:02:35.319
But simplifying the game by using the screen off the ball

00:02:35.319 --> 00:02:38.719
to put myself in pockets to be able to catch and shoot.

00:02:38.719 --> 00:02:40.840
If I could figure out how to do that with my game,

00:02:40.840 --> 00:02:42.879
it'll take my game to another level.

00:02:42.879 --> 00:02:47.079
It'll make us a better team, and the sky's the limit.

00:02:47.079 --> 00:02:50.400
